Senator Barbara A. Mikulski's retirement from the United States Senate is acknowledged by President Obama in this statement. He describes her as an institution in the Senate and praises her decades-long service to the people of Maryland. Mikulski is recognized as the longest-serving woman in Congress, and her leadership is seen as an inspiration for women and girls worldwide. The President highlights Mikulski's role as Chairwoman and Vice Chairwoman of the Senate's Appropriations Committee, emphasizing her commitment to reflecting values in budget decisions. He commends her advocacy for paycheck fairness, childcare, healthcare, education, women's rights, and other issues that have strengthened American families. The President expresses his anticipation of working with Senator Mikulski in the next two years and extends his best wishes for her future endeavors.